title: Is Roxy Mitchell still ALIVE? EastEnders star tipped for shock comeback
text:
They drowned in the pool of the hotel where Jack married Ronnie, with Ronnie dying trying to save her little sister. 
But did Roxy actually die? 
Since they've died the whole of Walford has been mourning Ronnie, especially because she left behind three children. 
In last night's episode Jack went to visit his wife in the funeral parlour, with actress Sam Womack making a return. 
bbc DEAD? Roxy has barely been mentioned in EastEnders lately Soap characters who came back from the dead Sunday, 29th November 2015 Charlie Slater need not worry about being written off the show as fellow Eastender Kathy Beale proved you can return from the dead in Soapland. See which other soap characters have mysteriously come back from the dead. 1 / 11 BBC/Kieron McCarron Following her 'death' in 2006, Kathy Beale made a surprise appearance in Walford in February this year, to EastEnders' 30th anniversary. She returned for a third time summer 
But where was Roxy? 
Towards the end of last night's instalment Phil Mitchell got a mystery phone call, which he told his wife Sharon was a "wrong number". 
But then he picked up the call and things got very suspicious. 
"Hello, I saw your missed call, why are you ringing so late?" he said. 
bbc TRAGIC: The sisters drowned on New Year's Day 
bbc WHO IS IT? Who was Phil talking to last night? “Of course I'll see you” Phil Mitchell 
"OK, alright calm down. Of course I'll see you. Alright I'll meet you there." 
Viewers had some theories about who could be on the other end of the call — with some predicting that it could be Roxy, who might secretly still be alive. 
"Anyone else thinking Phil's secret caller was Roxy?" one viewer tweeted. 
Another posted: "Really thought Phil's secret phone call was going to be Ronnie or Roxy." 
bbc SO SAD: We've seen Ronnie's body but not Roxy's Conclusive proof that these dead celebrities are ALIVE? Monday, 16th January 2017 People have doubted the deaths of famous people since famous people started dying. Are these sightings proof that they faked their own deaths? 1 / 6 Getty/Youtube A Youtube video (right) alleges that the picture is a selfie taken by Tupac Shakur on a mobile phone from 2011 
"Wait... What if Phil's mystery caller was Roxy?" a third said. 
EastEnders does have a history of bringing characters back from the dead, with Kathy Beale returning in 2015 after over a decade away. 
But (sadly) it seems highly unlikely that Roxy is still alive as her death was highly publicised, with actress Rita Simons admitting that she wanted to move on from the BBC soap. 
EastEnders continues tonight at 8pm on BBC One. Related articles
